{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 13,
  "title": "第十三章（寵辱）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "寵辱若驚，貴大患若身。"
    },
    {
      "text": "何謂寵辱若驚？寵之為下。得之若驚，失之若驚。是謂寵辱若驚。"
    },
    {
      "text": "何謂貴大患若身？吾所以有大患者，為吾有身也。及吾无身，有何患？"
    },
    {
      "text": "故貴為身於為天下，若可以托天下矣。愛以身為天下，如可以寄天下矣。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "貴，畏也。若，至也。謂大患至身，故皆驚。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "問何謂寵，何謂辱。寵者尊榮，辱者恥辱。及身還自問者，以曉人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 29,
          "end": 29
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "辱為下賤。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 19,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "得寵榮驚者，處高位如臨深危也。貴不敢驕，富不敢奢。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "失者，失寵處辱也。驚者，恐禍重來也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 30,
          "end": 31
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "解上得之若驚，失之若驚。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "復還自問：何故畏大患至身。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "吾所以有大患者，為吾有身。有身憂者，勤勞念其飢寒，觸情從慾，則遇禍患也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 31,
          "end": 31
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "使吾無有身體，得道自然，輕舉昇雲，出入無間，與道通神，當有何患。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言人君貴其身而賤人，欲為天下主者，則可寄立，不可以久也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言人君能愛其身，非為己也，乃欲為萬民之父母。以此得為天下主者，乃可以託其身於萬民之上，長無咎也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 11,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "寵必有辱，榮必有患，驚辱等、榮患同也。為下得寵辱榮患若驚，則不足以亂天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大患，榮寵之屬也。生之厚，必入死之地，故謂之大患也。人迷之於榮寵，返之於身，故曰大患若身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "由有其身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 24,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "歸之自然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無以易其身，故曰貴也。如此乃可以託天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無物可以損其身，故曰愛也。如此乃可以寄天下也。不以寵辱榮患損易其身，然後乃可以天下付之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
